message.content: One of the most significant events that occurred in Saint Lucia in the past five years was the opening of the Hewanorra International Airport's new terminal in 2020. The new terminal, which cost approximately $175 million, aimed to enhance the country's tourism industry and improve the overall travel experience for visitors. The modern facility includes expanded immigration and customs areas, increased retail and dining options, and improved passenger amenities. This development was a crucial step in Saint Lucia's efforts to attract more tourists and boost its economy.
